                        "center": "HQ",
                        "date_created": "2024-07-19T00:00:00Z",
                        "description": "“Space can unite a troubled country in troubled times. And no moment united the country quite like when the Eagle landed, as all of planet Earth watched from below.”    For the 55th anniversary of the Apollo 11 Moon landing, and in the midst of times that recall the era when the Moon landing took place, NASA Administrator Bill Nelson shares a message on the special power of space to bring people together—and the hope that this anniversary will be a time for reflection and healing.",
